HEADWORD: Performer
<hw>Per*form"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who performs,
accomplishes, or fulfills; <as>as, a good promiser, but a bad
<ex>performer</ex></as>; especially, one who shows skill and training in
any art; <as>as, a <ex>performer</ex> of the drama; a <ex>performer</ex>
on the harp.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perfricate</ent>⟦br⟧
